&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Product Manager to join our Creation Engine pillar, the foundational teams that power Figma&#39;s canvas, rendering, performance, and extensions across all products. This role sits at the intersection of cutting-edge web technology, creative tools, and AI innovation, building the foundation that enables millions of designers and developers to create and collaborate in ways that weren&#39;t possible before. You&#39;ll lead two critical teams, SceneGraph &amp;amp; Sync and Fullscreen Platform, driving the core data model, real-time collaboration infrastructure, and platform foundations that power all Figma products across web, desktop, and mobile.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full time role that can be held from one of our US hubs or remotely in the United States.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;What you’ll do at Figma:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and drive the product vision, strategy, and roadmap for foundational data model, collaboration, and platform systems that power all Figma products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide the SceneGraph &amp;amp; Sync team to optimize core data representation, real-time collaboration infrastructure, and AI integration capabilities including Figma&#39;s proprietary AI language&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide the Fullscreen Platform team in developing C++ foundations, WASM loading, developer APIs, and headless rendering capabilities that enable internal teams to build on Figma&#39;s platform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape the company strategy for version control, real-time collaboration, and platform foundations, ensuring consistency and performance across all products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with product teams as a technical consultant, providing specialized platform capabilities while maintaining architectural integrity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive performance optimization initiatives around file load times, collaboration sync, and platform efficiency to deliver performant user experiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex technical concepts for non-technical stakeholders and communicate the value of foundational improvements across the organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;section page-centered&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;We&#39;d love to hear from you if you have:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years of experience as a full-time Product Manager&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong technical background with understanding of version control systems, distributed systems, or real-time collaboration technologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with building internal APIs, developer platforms, and foundational systems that enable other teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to balance immediate performance improvements with long-term architectural investments in platform systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent cross-functional collaboration skills and ability to navigate ambiguity while building roadmaps and aligning stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;While not required, it’s an added plus if you also have:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with LLMs or AI integration in complex software systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of complex design tools or creative software platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background in multiplayer systems and conflict resolution algorithms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with WebAssembly (WASM), C++, or low-level performance optimization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of browser technologies and cross-platform development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading major platform initiatives that enabled multiple product teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;section page-centered&quot;&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;At Figma, one of our values is Grow as you go. We believe in hiring smart, curious people who are excited to learn and develop their skills. If you’re excited about this role but your past experience doesn’t align perfectly with the points outlined in the job description, we encourage you to apply anyways. You may be just the right candidate for this or other roles.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Pay Transparency Disclosure&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
